          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-10-21T14:26:09Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Fairness in Political Advertising Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill requires radio and television broadcasters to make free broadcast time available for political advertising.</p> <p>Specifically, during an election year, broadcasters generally must&nbsp;allot at least two hours of free broadcast time to each qualified political candidate in a statewide or national election. A broadcaster that&nbsp;fails or refuses to comply with the bill shall not have its&nbsp;license or franchise renewed. </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2019-01-30T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
